  * Generate system documentation from an org-mode source of truth at build
    time. doc/man/*.org are the per-command man-page sources (pandoc → groff);
    doc/dsmr-localfirst.org is the topic manual (TL;DR, theory of operation,
    usage examples, configuration, extension points, gotchas/debugging) and is
    exported to a GNU info manual (emacs ox-texinfo → makeinfo) and an HTML
    documentation page (emacs ox-html). The previous hand-written groff man
    pages are removed; org is now the single source.
  * Build-Depends on emacs-nox | emacs, texinfo, pandoc (generators only — the
    production package ships the static man/info/HTML and needs none of them).

