dsmr-localfirst (1.0-7) trixie; urgency=low

  * Docs only. SPEC: document the eligibility contract's fastforward refinement
    — clause 2 validates an alias catch-all of the form "| fastforward <cdb>"
    against that cdb (targets :L@domain, :@domain, :L@) so unknown system
    recipients are rejected at RCPT, and the recipient domain is part of the
    predicate input. DEPLOY: note the cdb-must-track-/etc/aliases maintenance
    rule (rebuild via newaliases), the "-p disables the reject" gotcha, and the
    optional DOMAIN argument to the system-identity probe.

